5 years, 4 cookbooks 💫 my babies! 

Working on each of these books has taught me so much and I wanted to share a few things with you- 

✨Getting started is the most important part
When the offer came to me for my first book in the year 2018, I thought I wasn't prepared enough and a sense of doubt was a constant companion. Even after taking up the offer many times, I felt stuck, however, by the end, it became the biggest learning curve in my life. The entire experience was surreal and a big milestone in my baking journey. So I would say that don't be intimidated by opportunities that come your way, grab them with open arms, without any worry as every adventure requires that first big step.

✨Everyone has a role to play in this journey
When I was working on the first book I was working all alone and didn't have a team back then. However, shortly I realized that it is impossible to do everything on your own if you want to grow and have a good quality product. I also realized that more than your strengths, you need to be aware of your weaknesses and delegate them to a team that can help you achieve your goals. After the first book, I started building a team and then they say the rest is history. My last three book writing journeys have been super smooth and enjoyable hence making it a rewarding process not only for me but my team as well.

✨Feedback is very important 
As an individual working on something that takes a long time, say about a year or two to produce, it becomes easy to develop a tunnel vision without realizing that the product needs constant feedback.
I always want the final product to be valuable to my audience and therefore I feel it is important to incorporate certain feedback while working on the product. Hence I would highly recommend keeping the feedback journey a continuous one in whatever aspect of your life you are present.
For example, for all my books I made it a point to send out the recipes to a couple of friends for a fresh perspective and understand the user journey up close. This has helped me take a pause and understand the minor tweaks I need to make so that the audiences enjoy the recipes to the fullest. 

To many more 💫

I loveee making desserts in boxes like these because it just makes the dessert so much more fun🥳  This cheesecake came out fantastic annndd, is a perfect no-bake recipe when you’re totally in the mood to cheat! Make this quick version while strawberries are still in season❤️

Ingredients :
🍓4-5 digestive biscuits
🍓1 cup whipped cream
🍓1/4 cup strawberry puree
🍓1/4 cup cream cheese
🍓1/4 cup white melted chocolate
🍓Fresh strawberries for decoration

Method:
1. Crush the digestive biscuits in a grinder and set the first layer in the box.
2. Cut fresh strawberries in half and stick them on the walls of the tub
3. For the filling, mix whipped cream, strawberry puree and cream cheese together
4. Pipe the filling over the biscuit layer.
5. Refrigerate the box for 1-2 hours and then pour a thin layer of melted white chocolate on top
6. Serve the tub when the chocolate hardens. Crack the top and dig in!

Is it just me, or do dessert cravings come faster on winter days? 🤔Well, if you can relate, then this is ‘for sure’ for youuuuu!! ✨ these eggless brownies need only 2 minutes in the microwave and are so yum 🍫 

🍫3/4 cup Biscoff spread
🍫1/2 cup butter
🍫1/2 cup dark chocolate
🍫1/2 cup yogurt
🍫2 tbsp sugar
🍫1/2 cup maida
🍫4 tbsp cocoa powder
🍫1 tsp baking powder
🍫Biscoff biscuits

Method:
1. Line a tray/mould with parchment paper. Spread an even layer of biscoff spread and freeze it for 2-3 hrs. 
2. Now in a microwave safe bowl, melt chocolate and butter. You could do this in the microwave or on the stove 
3. Mix in the yogurt and sugar. 
4. To this add maida, baking powder, cocoa powder.
5. Mix well
6. Transfer half of the batter to a lined 5”x 5” microwave safe glass dish. Put the frozen biscoff layer and pour the remaining batter on it. 
7. Top with some biscoff biscuits.
8. Cook this in the microwave on regular heating mode for 2 mins.

On my trip to London this December, I discovered this viral honey butter toast that they do at Arome Bakery. This is my take on it and it’s filled with Nutella and bananas ❤️ 
If indulgent breakfasts are your thing, try this out 
🙋🏻‍♂️ 

Ingredients: 
🍞2 Bread Slices 
🍞2-4 tbsp Nutella
🍞Banana slices
🍞4 tbsp Light Brown Sugar
🍞4 tbsp Butter, softened

Method: 
1.  Spread a generous layer of nutella on one slice of bread followed by thinly sliced banana and sandwich it with another slice of bread. 
2. Mix softened butter and sugar together until it’s combined. 
3. Spread this mixture on both sides of the sandwich. 
4. Place the sandwich on a slightly heated saucepan and cook untill it’s golden brown. 
5. Serve warm

Sorry about my voice today but hey, weekend breakkie sorted🫶🫶These pancake bombs are filled with yummy Nutella and can make for a perfect weekend breakfast✨✨
The best part is that this is an eggless recipe, made with whole wheat flour and issuper simple to make❤️

Ingredients 
1 cup + 2tbsp warm milk
1/2 tbsp vinegar
1 cup whole wheat flour 
2 tbsp sugar
1/2 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp vanilla extract 
2 tbsp oil
Nutella, as required 

Method:

1. Combine milk and vinegar together and set aside for a few mins. This will turn into buttermilk.
2. In another bowl, add all the dry ingredients and whisk well to combine. 
3. Make a well in the middle and add buttermilk and oil.
4. Combine well to make a smooth pancake batter.
5. Now, heat the pan and lightly brush it with butter or oil.
6. Pour some pancake batter into the cavities till half filled.
7. Carefully, pipe the nutella in the centre of this pancake batter and cover it again with the remaining pancake batter.
8. Flip and cook on both the sides till a golden crispy texture is achieved.
9. Plate them in your favourite dish and dust some icing sugar on top.
Your decadent pancake bombs are ready. Enjoy !

Treated myself to the world’s best Eggless Donuts! 🍩😍 These donuts don’t just satiate your sweet cravings but leave you wonderstruck by the ease with which they come to life. The cooking becomes joyously simple with @stahl_india’s Artisan Hybrid Kadhai. Perfect pour, heat-resistant handles, ideal weight, and even heat distribution are just some of the advantages of this versatile cookware! ✨ Tryyyy this recipe todayy and thank me later! 😉

Ingredients:
1 cup Warm Milk
¾ tsp Instant Dry Yeast
2 tbsp Sugar
2 + ¼ cup All-Purpose Flour
¼ cup Melted Butter 
Oil, for frying

Filling:
Pastry Cream / Custard Filling 

Caramel Top:
1 cup Sugar 
¼ cup Water 

Method:
1. Add flour, sugar, yeast, milk, and melted butter in a bowl. Knead the dough using a stand mixer or your hands till it all comes together and forms a smooth, non-sticky dough. 
Do the windowpane test to check if the dough is ready.
2. Line another bowl with oil and place the rolled dough carefully in it. Cover it with a damp cloth and let it proof in a warm place for 1-2 hours till it is doubled in size.
3. Once the dough is double in size, knock down the dough and place it on a floured surface to knead again. 
4. Knead for a minute and divide it into equal portions (70-75g each) 
5. Place these divided dough balls onto parchment paper and let it proof again for another 30-60 mins till doubled in size.
6. Heat the oil for frying and once it is hot enough, carefully fry the doughnuts on each side till a nice golden brown colour is achieved. 
7. While the doughnuts are cooling, make the caramel for the top coating in a heavy bottom pan using the given quantities.
8. Make small holes on either side of the doughnuts and fill them with pastry cream or custard using a piping bag. 
9. Carefully dip the top of the doughnuts in the caramel till it’s nicely coated and let it cool for a few mins.

Your eggless doughnuts are ready! Enjoy!

This 60 seconds cookie is eggless, tasty, crumbly, chocolaty and ooozing with Nutella! 
Its perfect for when you are lazy to make anything extensive and will definitely make your dessert time a treat 🙌🏻✨

Ingredients:
🍪2 tbsp butter
🍪1 tbsp caster sugar
🍪1/2 tsp vanilla extract
🍪1/4 cup all-purpose flour
🍪1 tbsp cocoa powder
🍪1/8 tsp baking soda
🍪3 tbsp nutella
🍪Milk and dark chocolate chips to top

Method:
1. In a bowl, take the softened butter and add caster sugar in it and mix properly.
2. Add vanilla extract into this and give it a good mix.
3. Into this, add all-purpose flour, cocoa powder and baking soda.
4. Mix this all together, till everything is properly combined and no flour specs are visible. 
5. Now make a round ball of nutella and put it inside the shaped dough. 
6. Place it over a parchment paper square and stick the milk and dark chocolate chips on it and freeze it for 15 minutes.
7. Once it hardens, place this into the microwave and set the timer to 60 seconds.
8. Once it is done, cool it for some time and enjoy your 60 second microwave cookie!

These fudge brownies have oreos on top and a layer of cream cheese in the middle and they taste SOOO good 🍫🍫❤️

Ingredients: 

1-1/2 cup cream cheese 
2 cup dark chocolate, coarsely chopped
1 cup butter
4 eggs
2 cup caster sugar
1 cup all purpose flour
6 tbsp cocoa powder
2 tsp baking powder

Method:
1. Line a tray/ mould with parchment paper. Spread an even layer of cream cheese and freeze it for 2-3 hrs. 
2. In a saucepan set over low heat, melt butter and chocolate. Let it cool.
3. Whisk sugar and eggs together. Add the cooled chocolate mixture.
4. Add in the flour, cocoa powder and baking powder.
5. Transfer half the batter to the baking dish and then put the frozen cream cheese layer. Now pour the remaining batter. 
6. Top it up with crushed oreo biscuits. 
7. Bake at 180C for 50-60 mins. Let the brownies cool completely before you try and cut them

Strawberries are still in season and I clearly haven’t had enough of them! If you too prefer your drinks to be flavourful, refreshing, and one that adds a good kick to your mood, then you cannot scroll past this recipe without giving it a shot! 

Ingredients:

4-5 strawberries
2 tbsp castor sugar
2 tbsp water
1/4 cup + 3/4 cup tapioca flour 
1/2 cup strawberry milk
2 fresh strawberries, chopped
Milk foam (optional)

Method:

1. Blend strawberries, water and sugar in a blender jar. Add red food colour at this stage, if you like. 
2. Transfer the mixture into a bowl and add 1/4 cup tapioca flour. 
3. Microwave for 1 min in 15 secs interval each. It will become sticky and thick. 
4. Now add the remaining 3/4 cup tapioca flour to form a dough.
5. Shape the dough into long, thin logs and cut equal portions. Take each portion and roll it into small balls using your palms.
6. Now, boil them in boiling water till they become shiny and somewhat translucent. This will take around 20-25 mins. 
7. Strain them and wash under cold running water to cool them down.
8. In a tall glass or a mason jar, add the boba pearls along with ice and chopped strawberries. 
9. Finish it off by pouring the strawberry milk and topping it with some milk foam.

Enjoy !

No cream cheese, no problem 🥳🥳
This eggless baked cheesecake is made without any cream cheese but still tastes equally good 🤌🏻🤌🏻 
I have used hung curd as a replacement and for 1.5 cup of hung curd you will need to hang about 3 cups of curd overnight! 

Make your #january delightful by trying out this cheesecake today! 

Ingredients : 
1 + 1/2 cup crushed lotus biscuits 
5 tbsp melted butter 
1 + 1/2 cup hung curd
1/2 cup heavy cream/fresh cream
1 cup condensed milk
2 tbsp cornflour 
Biscoff spread (for topping)
Whipped cream (for garnish)
Lotus biscuit crumbs ( for garnish)

Method :
1. In a large bowl, add the crushed biscuits with melted butter and combine till all the crumbs are coated.
2. Transfer the biscuit base into a lined springform pan and using the back of a spoon, press down to form an even cheesecake base. Refrigerate for 15-20 mins.
3. Meanwhile in another bowl, add hung curd, cream, condensed milk and cornflour. Whisk everything together just until a smooth batter is formed with no lumps.
4. Pour this cheesecake batter over the chilled biscuit base and transfer the springform pan into a larger baking dish. Pour hot water into the larger dish to create a hot water bath.
5. Bake this in a pre-heated oven at 170 degree Celsius for 40-45 mins.
6. Once baked, refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight. 
7. Once set, finish it off by spreading a generous layer of biscoff spread, some whipped cream dollops and sprinkling crush biscuits over it.
